Better subgroup calibration in the ensemble than the C15 trained models is also evident in Supplementary Figures S10–S12 for indicators of suicide, selected mental health diagnoses and treatments, and the demographic variables of race, ethnicity, gender, and age. When models are well-calibrated, the score histograms will accurately reflect the risk histogram of observed cases for each subgroup. Thus we can observe in Supplementary Figure S10 that a diagnosis of suicide ideation in any time bin increases the risk score by \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
